cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the robustness of image classifiers to temporal perturbations derived from videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also evaluates a diverse array of classifiers pre-trained on ImageNet, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the challenges of deploying convolutional neural networks in environments that require both reliable and low-latency predictions, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper constructs two datasets, ImageNet-Vid-Robust and YTBB-Robust, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the errors in detection models, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
